## Modular Code Structure

### Size Thresholds

| Metric | Limit | Rationale |
|--------|-------|-----------|
| **File Length** | 300 lines max | Scrapers have verbose selectors |
| **Function** | 50 lines max | Single responsibility |
| **Transformer** | 250 lines max | Per-platform data mapping |
| **Scraper class** | 200 lines max | Browser automation only |
| **Parameters** | 6 max | Use typed objects (`TransformContext`, `IScraperConfig`) |
| **Nesting Depth** | 3 levels max | Extract helpers |

### When Limits Are Exceeded
```
If Transformer > 250 lines:
  → Split by entity type (e.g., transformCourses(), transformAssignments())
  → Keep the main export as a thin orchestrator

If Scraper > 200 lines:
  → Extract page-object helpers (e.g., loginPage.fill(), gradesPage.extract())
  → Keep lifecycle methods thin

If Function > 50 lines:
  → Extract helper functions
  → Pure helpers are easier to test (M1)
```

## Violation Response
When violation detected:
1. REJECT with mandate number (M1-M9)
2. Show bad code vs good code
3. Reference relevant file
4. Provide fix instruction

